result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathaniel Tate was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Nathaniel Tate is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Nathaniel Tate was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Nathaniel Tate in court with attorney Craig J. Johnson.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
cab
As to count 1:
Pursuant to negotiations and on motion of the state, court ordered count 1 dismissed.
As to count 2:
 Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Criminal Complaint  and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.
.
  Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  Court sentenced the defendant to serve 50 days in the House of Correction with credit for 1 day served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 6 months with the following conditions:
- AODA assessment; comply with any treatment, if needed.
- No contact with firearms.
- In lieu of paying the costs and surcharges, the court ordered the defendant to complete 50 hours of community service.
 
Received and filed: Pretrial Sentence Credit, Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief, Memorandum of Conditions of Probation.
